<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:views="clr-namespace:Ben.Views"
             x:Class="Ben.Views.HelpPage"
             x:DataType="views:HelpPage"
             x:Name="RootHelpPage"
             Title="Help">

       <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
              <BackButtonBehavior IsVisible="False"/>
       </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

       <Grid Style="{DynamicResource PaperRootGrid}">
              <Grid Padding="16"
                    HorizontalOptions="Fill"
                    RowDefinitions="Auto,*,Auto"
                    RowSpacing="12">

                     <Label Grid.Row="0"
                            Text="How to use Ben"
                            Style="{DynamicResource SectionTitle}"
                            HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>

                     <Border Grid.Row="1"
                             Style="{DynamicResource ThemedCard}"
                             StrokeThickness="{DynamicResource DividerThickness}">
                            <Border.StrokeShape>
                                   <RoundRectangle CornerRadius="{DynamicResource ListCardCornerRadius}"/>
                            </Border.StrokeShape>
                            <ScrollView BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource WritingPaper}">
                                   <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16"
                                                        Spacing="24"
                                                        BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource WritingPaper}">

                                          <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="8">
                                                 <Label Text="What Is Ben?"
                                                        Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>
                                                 <Label Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                                        Text="Ben is a modern, digital interpretation of the classic Franklin planning method. Instead of scattering your life across sticky notes, apps, and inboxes, Ben gives you a single place to plan your day, capture your notes, track your progress, and stay aligned with what matters most.&#x0a;&#x0a;Each day in Ben has its own dedicated page with a prioritized task list, a flexible notes section, and tools for forwarding, organizing, and reviewing your work.&#x0a;&#x0a;Ben is not just a to-do list. It is a daily planning ritual designed to help you think, act, and follow through with clarity."/>
                                          </VerticalStackLayout>

                                          <BoxView HeightRequest="1"
                                                   BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource Line}"/>

                                          <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="8">
                                                 <Label Text="Why Ben Is Better"
                                                        Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>
                                                 <Label Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                                        Text="Most to-do apps encourage you to accumulate tasks, not complete them. Lists get long, priorities blur, and important items get buried.&#x0a;&#x0a;Ben solves that:&#x0a;&#x0a;- Daily focus: plan one day at a time, not an endless backlog.&#x0a;- Prioritization: A/B/C levels identify what is essential vs. optional.&#x0a;- Forwarding with intention: tasks move forward with context so nothing slips.&#x0a;- Integrated notes: thoughts and ideas live right next to your tasks.&#x0a;- A planning rhythm: review, prioritize, execute every day.&#x0a;&#x0a;The result: fewer forgotten commitments, clearer priorities, and a calmer mind."/>
                                          </VerticalStackLayout>

                                          <BoxView HeightRequest="1"
                                                   BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource Line}"/>

                                          <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="8">
                                                 <Label Text="Your Daily Task List"
                                                        Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>
                                                 <Label Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                                        Text="Each day begins with a clean page. Open today's page, tap Add Task, enter a clear title, assign an A/B/C priority, and save.&#x0a;&#x0a;Tips:&#x0a;- Keep tasks actionable. Write &quot;Email Sarah about budget&quot; not just &quot;Sarah&quot;.&#x0a;- Break large items into smaller steps.&#x0a;- Limit A-priority tasks to what you can realistically finish today.&#x0a;&#x0a;Your daily list becomes the backbone of your plan."/>
                                          </VerticalStackLayout>

                                          <BoxView HeightRequest="1"
                                                   BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource Line}"/>

                                          <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="8">
                                                 <Label Text="Task Statuses"
                                                        Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>
                                                 <Label Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                                        Text="Update any task with a single tap:&#x0a;&#x0a;- Open: not started yet&#x0a;- In Progress: you have begun&#x0a;- Completed: finished today&#x0a;- Forwarded: moved to a future date&#x0a;- Dropped: no longer needed&#x0a;&#x0a;Statuses tell the story of your day at a glance."/>
                                          </VerticalStackLayout>

                                          <BoxView HeightRequest="1"
                                                   BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource Line}"/>

                                          <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="8">
                                                 <Label Text="Forwarding Tasks"
                                                        Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>
                                                 <Label Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                                        Text="Tap a task, choose Forward, and pick a new date. Ben marks the original as Forwarded and creates a fresh copy on that date.&#x0a;&#x0a;Missed a few days? Use Catch-Up Mode. Open any past date and forward unfinished tasks in bulk or one by one. Nothing gets lost, even when life gets busy."/>
                                          </VerticalStackLayout>

                                          <BoxView HeightRequest="1"
                                                   BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource Line}"/>

                                          <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="8">
                                                 <Label Text="Notes"
                                                        Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>
                                                 <Label Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                                        Text="Every day includes a free-form notes area for meeting notes, ideas, journaling, or anything that is not quite a task. Notes stay tied to the day they were created.&#x0a;&#x0a;To turn a note into a task, highlight the text, tap Create Task, assign a priority, and save. Important ideas never get lost."/>
                                          </VerticalStackLayout>

                                          <BoxView HeightRequest="1"
                                                   BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource Line}"/>

                                          <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="8">
                                                 <Label Text="Your Daily Planning Session"
                                                        Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>
                                                 <Label Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                                        Text="Step 1: Review yesterday. Mark completed items, forward unfinished tasks, review notes for follow-ups.&#x0a;&#x0a;Step 2: Build today's list. Add forwarded tasks, add new ones, assign priorities. Keep the A-list short.&#x0a;&#x0a;Step 3: Focus. Start with A-priority tasks, capture thoughts in notes, update statuses as you go.&#x0a;&#x0a;This daily ritual keeps you aligned and ensures nothing falls through the cracks."/>
                                          </VerticalStackLayout>

                                          <BoxView HeightRequest="1"
                                                   BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource Line}"/>

                                          <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="8">
                                                 <Label Text="Projects"
                                                        Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"/>
                                                 <Label Style="{DynamicResource Handwriting}"
                                                        LineBreakMode="WordWrap"
                                                        Text="Not everything belongs on a daily page. Projects give structure to work that spans weeks or months: initiatives, home renovations, vacations, events, or long-term goals.&#x0a;&#x0a;Each project has its own task list and notes section. Pull tasks from a project into your daily plan whenever you are ready to act on them."/>
                                          </VerticalStackLayout>

                                   </VerticalStackLayout>
                            </ScrollView>

                     </Border>

                     <Button Grid.Row="2"
                             Text="Back"
                             Style="{DynamicResource SecondaryActionButton}"
                             HeightRequest="44"
                             Clicked="OnBackClicked"/>
              </Grid>
       </Grid>

</ContentPage>